Basic intro to transformers

Most modern LLM archi depends on the transformers archi.

- transformers archi is most needed.

takes input.
preprcoessing text - Input texts into tokens each token has id.
Encoders - takes input text(tokens) data and produce text encodings
Vector Embeddings - converts those all tokens into Vectors - here symantic meanings between words and captured just like KNN.

transformer archi mainly consists of :
- Encoders - encodes input text into Vectors
- Decoder - generates output text from Vectors

A note of self-attention mechanism:
- Key part of transformers  allows model to weigh importance of diff words/tokens relative to each other.
- This enables models capture long range of dependencies
- above two are key parts of the predicts of next words or tokens.

Variations of transformer models
- BERT - Bi-directional encoder representations from transformers -- predicts hidden words in a given sentence
- GPT models - generative pretrained transformers - Generates new words.

BERT - can do very well of sentimental analysis and also it can find hidden words and also give attention to every word. it can look from both sides - depth understanding - it has encoder
GPT - it looks sentence from left to right - it has decoder.


transformers vs LLMs
- Not all transformers are LLMs
- transformers are also used for CV.

CNN vs transformers
- for vision related tasks VIt is performing better than CNN.

- Not all LLMs are transformers.
- LLMs can be based on recurrent or CNN as well.


How will models know the which words are important - based on the context.
But how will models know about the context.


transformers - what why and how?

- before transformers NLP models read the words one by one, but current word understand previous words has no idea. it only needs to understand the current words.
- so its impossible find relationships between words withour the previous memory.

- transformers make entire sentences can read a at once.
- that makes attention to read entire words and find the contexts.
- process texts much faster, because they are not limited to word by word.


what is a transformer?
- A transformer is a type of computer model that reads the whole sentence in one go., understanding which words are important and relation between them.


How is works?
- Step-1: Representing words with Embeddings and positions
-- transformers start by Turning each word in a sentence into set of numbers(Embeddings)  that Represents the meaning of the words.
-- they also add positions to the each word to keep track of the order of the words in the sentence.

ex: dog chasing the ball.

- step-2: Using attention to find important works
-- The transformer then uses attention to find the most important words for understanding the meaning.
-- attention scores tell which words relate most closely to each other.

ex: In the sentence,
- the dog,  tired after running , chased the ball.

tired after is the extra information running and chased or important which has more attention scores.

ex: who chases the ball?  dog by attention.

- Step-3: Layers to build understanding
-- transformers have layers, each layer acts like a filters that focuses on the different aspects of the sentence.
-- In the first layer it understands the basic relationships like dog and chased.
-- but in next layers it might understand "chased by the ball" is involved by the dog.
-- in every layer of transformer improves the understanding context.

-- Google translate has transformers can easily understand the basic relationships across all the languages so they can easily understands the contexts better even how worst the task is.